720723f-a.title: Manhattan: Kenmare Street - Cleveland Place
720723f-a.text:
Kenmare Street, north side, east from and including Cleveland (Marion Street) Place. Note the Williamsburg Bridge at the eastern end of Delancey (a continuation of Kenmare Street, east of the Bowery) Street.
Agril 19, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.

720724f-a.title: Manhattan: Kenmare Street - Cleveland Place
720724f-a.text:
Kenmare Street, north side, east from, but not including Cleveland
Place.
April 19, 1935.
L. Sperr.
720724f-a.folder: Kenmare Street & Cleveland Place, Manhattan, NY

718990f-b.title: Manhattan: Cleveland Place - Kenmare Street
718990f-b.text:
(1)
Cleveland Place (M(arion Street), east side, north from, but not incluuding Kenmare, to and including Spring Streets, as seen from Lefaette (Elm) Street. Shown on the S.E. corner of Cleveland Place, at Spring Street, is the East River Savings Bank Building. ( No. 60-62 Spring St.)
April 19, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, as seen from Eenmare Street, showing a station of the Free
Milk Fund for Babies on the north side of Eenmare Street.
March 16, 1934.
P. L. Sperr.
